.help gemdate June2005 gemini.gemtools
.ih
NAME
gemdate -- Get FITS formatted date string
.ih
USAGE
gemdate
.ih
PARAMETERS
.ls zone = "UT"   (UT|local)
Return either the UT or the local date.
.le
.ls verbose = no
Print the date string to the screen.
.le
.ls outdate = ""
Return FITS formatted date string.  This is set by the task.
.le
.ls status = 0
Exit status will be non-zero if GEMDATE halted with an error.  This 
parameter is always set by the task and should not be modified by the user.
.le
.ih
DESCRIPTION
GEMDATE is an easy way to obtain the current time as a FITS formatted date 
string.  By default, the UT date is returned.  Whether \fIverbose\fR is turn 
on or not, the date string is always stored in the \fIoutdate\fR parameter.
.ih
EXAMPLES
1. Print the current UT date and time FITS string to the screen.
.sp
.nf
    ge> gemdate verbose+
.fi
.sp
2. Print the current local date and time FITS string to the screen.
.sp
.nf
    ge> gemdate zone=local verbose+
.fi
.sp
3. In a script, add the GEM-TLM time stamp.
.sp
.nf
    cache ("gemdate")
    gemdate ()
    nhedit (l_output//"[0]", "GEM-TLM", gemdate.outdate, 
        "UT Last modification with GEMINI")    
.fi
.ih
BUGS AND LIMITATIONS
.ih
SEE ALSO
.endhelp
